Usage of Duck Yeah! is governed by the End User License Agreement (EULA) present
in $APP_HOME/appserver/static/LICENSE.md for individual accounts or an Enterprise
Agreement for shared/corporate accounts. Duck Yeah! is presented through Splunkbase
for ease of distribution. In the event of a conflict of terms, the following
precedence applies:

    1. Enterprise Agreement
    2. EULA (defined above)
    3. What Inverse Tachyon says (per written agreement prior to service start or as
        amended by both parties in writing).
    4. What nth degree says (per written agreement prior to service start or as amended
        by both parties in writing).
    5. What Bear the cat says (by literally any vocalization).

Depending on with whom your contract resides - Inverse Tachyon or nth degree, 
points 3/4 may change precedence. The entity from whom you receive your invoices takes
precedence.

No matter what, if no superseding agreement exists, if Bear opines his word is
law. Like Rocket to Groot, Paul Stout shall be the sole interpreter of what
"mrrrOOOOWWOOWWW" means.

We are Groot.
